Detailed Description

A description of an Demand and target action to perform with it. 

 //get PendingDemand with getPage and FLAG_UPDATE_CURRENT flag
 PendingDemand* pPd = PendingDemand::getPageN(
     *context, *pIntent, PendingDemand::FLAG_UPDATE_CURRENT);

Member Enumeration Documentation

anonymous enum
Enumerator:
FLAG_ONE_SHOT 

Flag for use with getPage, getBroadcast, and getDelegate: this PendingDemand can only be used once.

FLAG_NO_CREATE 

Flag for use with getPage, getBroadcast, and getDelegate: if the described PendingDemand does not already exist, then simply return null instead of creating it.

FLAG_CANCEL_CURRENT 

Flag for use with getPage, getBroadcast, and getDelegate: if the described PendingDemand already exists, the current one is canceled before generating a new one.

You can use this to retrieve a new PendingDemand when you are only changing the extra data in the Demand; by canceling the previous pending demand, this ensures that only entities given the new data will be able to launch it. If this assurance is not an issue, consider FLAG_UPDATE_CURRENT.

FLAG_UPDATE_CURRENT 

Flag for use with getPage, getBroadcast, and getDelegate: if the described PendingDemand already exists, then keep it but its replace its extra data with what is in this new Demand.

This can be used if you are creating intents where only the extras change, and don't care that any entities that received your previous PendingDemand will be able to launch it with your new extras even if they are not explicitly given to it.
